### Closure on Prop

- When a function prop is expected to receive parameters is should be followed by `()=>foo`
- The `()=>foo(param)` can be called either from the parent or the child
- When called from the parent this should be on the generate element function, then the child should just call `prop.foo`


```jsx

//  Event Trigger Function
   function toggle(id) {
        console.log(id)
    }

//  Parent Component
    const boxStack = current.map(element => <Box key={element.id}  on={element.on} toggle={()=> toggle(element.id)}/>) 



//   Child Component

return (

        <div className="box" style={styles} onClick={prop.toggle} >
            <p>{prop.id}</p>
        </div>
    )
```
